rComments: Great, clear prof. Use his powerpoint lecture notes instead of the textbook. And prepare some questions before office hours before the midterm, to learn all the midterm material last minute.

I had civ100 with him and I actually had this course with other profs as well :( but let me tell you this, he is definitely, undoubtedly the best prof. He is very organized, clear, and extremely extremely helpful. And not only for civ100, he is definitely one of the best teacher I had in school :)

Better off not buying the textbook at all. His powerpoints (all of which are posted online at the beginning of the year) are all you'll need to do well. While he's really good at explaining, I recommend doing the Prep101 courses before midterms and exams. JZ+Prep101 is a lethal combination that will get you excellent marks! :D
